  "text": "Fisher's exact tests of the association between adaptive positions and classification of PSD95 pdz3 positions by sector, positional conservation, or spatial proximity were carried out using MATLAB. Positional conservation and sector were defined as reported previously [CITATION_1] , and spatial proximity was computed using coordinates from a high-resolution crystal structure of PSD95 pdz3 (PDB: 1BE9 (Doyle et al., 1996) ) as the closest distance between any pair of atoms of ligand T-2 and every other amino acid; see Figure S5 for tables and the contingency matrices.",
